Ernst Toch (pronounced [to ú]) (7 December 1887 - 1 October 1964) was a composer of classical music and film scores.
In 1909, his chamber symphony in F major (written 1906) won the Frankfurt/Main Mozart prize.
Toch won the Pulitzer Prize for Music in 1956 for his Third Symphony (premiered by the Pittsburgh Symphony Orchestra on December 2, 1955).
